HEADWORD: Chyluria
<hw>Chy*lu"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. from Gr.
<?/ chyle + <?/ urine.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A morbid condition
in which the urine contains chyle or fatty matter, giving it a milky
appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
